        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 5:10AM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 510 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Glenville to near
Rotterdam Junction to Schenectady. Movement was northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Schenectady, Clifton Park, Rotterdam, Saratoga Springs, Amsterdam,
Scotia, Mechanicville, Glenville, Niskayuna, Ballston Spa, Waterford,
Hagaman, Round Lake, Galway, Rotterdam Junction, East Glenville,
Burnt Hills, Rock City Falls, Country Knolls, and North Ballston Spa.

People attending Saratoga Performing Arts Center (SPAC) should seek
safe shelter immediately!

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 90 between exits 26 and 27.
Interstate 890 between exits 1a and 9.
Interstate 87 between exits 8A and 13N.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
